In a 10- to 12-inch frying pan over medium-high heat, cook onion and garlic in oil, stirring, until tinged brown; deglaze pan with 1 tablespoon of the broth. Add tomato sauce, remaining broth, banana, chili powder, cocoa, cinnamon, cumin, pepper, and cayenne. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer, covered, 10 minutes. Add chicken; continue to simmer until no longer pink in center of thickest part (cut to test), about 15 minutes longer. Put a breast half over rice on each of 4 plates. Spoon sauce and sprinkle almonds and raisins over portions. Offer tortillas alongside.